<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-03T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-03T14:00:00-05:00" n="525" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d525">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">511.4A6/375: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chairman of the American Delegation</hi>
                                (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-03T15:00:00-04:00">July 3, 1931—3
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>15. Your telegram 34, July 2, 10 a.m. Matter receiving consideration.
                            Meanwhile Department desires Delegation’s comment and
                            recommendations.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>